# Prophecy Self-Fulfilled

```
Years and years
                and years
                                and years
Of watching helplessly as you
        brutalized
        endlessly
        your soul
Accepting only pain and ugliness for yourself
Rejecting all praise and
        anything
that told you your worth

        It doesn’t count if your mother says it
she’s supposed to
        It doesn’t count if your father says it
he probably doesn’t mean it anyway
        Your teacher?
hates you, but only
        in your head

The only people permitted to tell you you’re beautiful
were those strangers who
        never knowing you
        never would

But every mistake you make’s
                a catastrophe
Every bruise you inflict
                shatters
The slightest bump as you pass
                sprawls
And you must surely be a wicked beast,
or so you say
in your head

Maybe if you tell yourself enough times that you’re intolerable
it eventually becomes
true.

But
even now
self-crowned the King of Monsters
You’re only a monster if you
                                bully
                        yourself into believing it
```


Written October 4, 2022


tags: poetry
